Probably the simplest way is to copy the diff out, remake the branch with a fresh checkout from master, and git push -f to the branch to update this pull request.

body:
@vivek-rane GitHub is showing a large diff from master and this change seems to duplicate a lot of existing commits there. I couldn't figure out why it's doing that. Mind trying to fix it?

Probably the simplest way is to copy the diff out, remake the branch with a fresh checkout from master, and `git push -f` to the branch to update this pull request.
